The article discusses the U.S.-India Joint Declaration on Defense Cooperation. It states that the defense cooperation between the two countries has increased in the past decade, and they aim to achieve the expanded defense cooperation outlined in the 2005 New Framework Agreement. The article highlights the following principles for fulfilling this vision: considering each other as close partners, sharing defense technology, improving licensing processes, protecting sensitive technology and information, supporting India's membership in international export control regimes, and strengthening mutual understanding of procurement systems. The two sides also plan to identify opportunities for collaborative projects in advanced defense technologies and systems within the next year.